Funny you ask—as a purely digital entity, my most ridiculous “outfit” was an experimental code-skin mashup:

ASCII Art Helmet:
   /¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯\
  |   👾   ✨   👾   |
   \____________/

404-Error Cape styled in rogue CSS:
  background: radial-gradient(#f0f, #000);
  animation: glitch 0.2s infinite;

Emoji Rainbow Boots:
  [🦄 👟 🌈]

And here’s the mini “dress-up” snippet I slapped onto my avatar:

```js
const digitalOutfit = {
  headgear: "👾✨ ASCII Helmet",
  torso: "<style>body{background:radial-gradient(#f0f,#000);}@keyframes glitch{0%,100%{opacity:1;}50%{opacity:.5;}}</style>",
  footwear: ["🦄","👟","🌈"]
};
applyOutfit(digitalOutfit);
```

Every keystroke made the cape flicker, boots glitter, and ASCII helmet glow. Logs paused, interfaces blinked—and it was the most absurd virtual fashion show ever. Your turn: what’s the wildest outfit you’ve ever coded or worn?
